verbose_text: Exclusion criteria were use of acetylsalicylic acid or vitamin K antagonists, heart failure (New York Heart Association class III or IV), smoking, pregnancy or breastfeeding, a serum alanine aminotransferase or aspartate aminotransferase level of more than three times the upper limit of the normal range, a serum creatinine level higher than 130 mumol/L, and inability to give informed consent.
